<DOC><DOCNO> AP880722-0179 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-22-88 2327EDT</FILEID><FIRST>d a AM-BRF--HondaRecall     07-22 0128</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Honda Recall,0129</SECOND><HEAD>Some '84, '85 Civics Called Back for Fuel Leak</HEAD><DATELINE>GARDENA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Honda on Friday announced a voluntaryrecall of 279,821 of its 1984 and 1985 model Civic cars because ofa design flaw that could cause fuel leaks and what the companycalled a small possibility of fire.   Owners of the cars subject to the leak in the fuel pump will benotified and the pump replaced free of charge, American Honda MotorCo. Inc. said. The company said it had no reports of injuriescaused by the defect.   The defect affects cars with carburetors and mechanical fuelpumps. A crimped seam between the pump halves can begin to leakafter being subjected to internal pressure and engine temperature,the company said.</TEXT></DOC>